Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @Red Chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded, finely chopped). Roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1/2%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop it into a #small bowl{}, along with the @Olive Oil for the Garlic Bread{2%tbsp}. Season with a little @salt{}, mix well and set aside.

In another small bowl, mix together the @Olive Oil for the Feta{1%tbsp}, chilli, @Honey{30%g} and @Dried Oregano{1%sachet}. Place the @Feta Cheese{200%g} in the centre of a large square of #foil{} (one block on top of the other). Pour the marinade over the feta, ensuring it is well coated. Scrunch up the foil to create a well-sealed parcel.

Pop the feta parcel onto one half of a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until warm and softened, ~{25-30%minutes}. When the feta has 5 mins left, pop the @Greek Style Flatbreads{2} onto the other half of the baking tray and drizzle over the garlic oil. Bake until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the oven and cut widthways into 2cm wide 'fingers'.

When ready, transfer the baked feta to a #serving dish{} (keep it in the foil). Sprinkle over the parsley and serve with the garlicky flatbread fingers alongside for scooping. Enjoy!